### [v0.3] - 2025-12-XX
#### Added
- Config::configurePrivacy(...) for defining whether to register logs or restrict what data to register.
- Collection and Item components for handling key-value pair arrays.
- ValidationWorker for validating data such as email addresses or passwords.
- ValidationFlags collection for handling validation flags.
- API Response success boolean field.
- AlreadyAuthorizedException for handling unauthorized exclusive endpoints.
- Endpoint argument unauthorizedExclusive for handling unauthorized exclusive endpoints.
- LogWorker::debug() for debugging system logs.
- MailWorker for sending crafted and dynamic emails.
- Mail component for crafting mail objects.
- Item::mail and Item::file for helping with Mail crafting.
- AUTH_DOMAIN env variable for defining global authorization domain.

#### Changed
- Skeleton: Update build.sh to account for last changes.
- DataWorker now uses Collection and Item components.
- Router now uses Collection and Item components.
- Template now uses Collection and Item components.
- PHP Version downgrade to 8.4 to support hosting deployment.
- System logs now are collapsed so they take less space.
- LogWorker prefix for each type of log.
- Template component now sanitazes file paths.
- AuthSlave::validateCSRF() now uses hash_equals() for improved security.

#### Fixed
- Skeleton: Sites folder not accounted for deploy.sh and index.php
- Skeleton: .htaccess fallback not working.
- Skeleton: Sites folder not accounted for watch.sh
- NotFoundException and NotAuthorizedException are not being handled correctly.
- ValidationWorker is not initialized. (jesus christ)
- DataWorker::getOne() crashes when no result is found.
- AlreadyAuthorizedException is not being handled.
- Config::configureAuthorization(...) is not enabling global authorization correctly.
- CSRF token session is not being correctly injected into the main template.

#### Removed
- htmlspecialchars method from Request::sanitizeData().
- meta tag HTTP headers from main.php Template.
- API Response status string field.
- domain configuration from Config::configureAuthorization(...)

---

### [v0.2] - 2025-12-06
#### Added
- Configuration of path redirects for 404 error.
- Support for .html template injection before and after #main div.
- Server::preload(__DIR__) for loading environment configuration.
- Server::getConfiguration(), Server::getTemplate(), Server::getViewRouter(), Server::getApiRouter() for modular loading.
- Test suite added.
- Feature to enable authorization across parent domain and all subdomains.
- Bee::getBaseDomain() and Bee::getBuiltDomain(...) for getting base domain and subdomain.
- Bee::hashPassword(...) and AuthWorker::autologin(...) for automatic password hashing and auto-login.
- AuthWorker::getAuthorizedUserId() for getting authorized user ID.
- New methods and uses for SQL queries in DataWorker and DataSlave.
- Deploy script for Apache.

#### Changed
- Template::oneline() is now Template::flex(), allowing for dynamic creation of templates.
- Improvement of HTML semantics for main.php.
- Server component is now a unique class with unique traits. Is not a component anymore.
- Bee::env method now supports default value if environment variable is not found.
- Improved URI parsing and path normalization.
- Improved Exception handling for easier maintenance.
- Standarization of JS native libraries (Lib class) for increased compatibility.
- Request::getDataItem() method has been optimized for better performance.
- Skeleton site structure is now insite sites/ folder.

#### Fixed
- Unauthorized redirect path not working for views, throws 403.
- Default JS function request not sending json data correctly.
- getDataItem() crashes when parsing array or objects.
- Unauthorized sites not redirecting to configured subdomain.

#### Removed
- Config $allowedHosts parameter. Couldn't find a real security use for this feature.